OL,7,FThe latest official figures, published
OL,8,Fearlier this month by the Ministry of
OL,9,FHousing, Communities and Local
OL,10,FGovernment, showed there were 123,100
OL,11,Fhouseholds in England in temporary
OL,12,Faccommodation in the three months to
OL,13,Fthe end of June - a rise of 16.3% on
OL,14,Fthe same period the previous year.
OL,16,FThere were 159,380 children in
OL,17,Ftemporary accommodation between April
OL,18,Fand June this year, those statistics
OL,19,Fshowed.
